| FR12: Recurring customer use cases | Epic 2-5: Integrated workflow |

## Epic List



## Epic 1: Frontend Homepage, Product, Blog, and Theme Updates

**Goal**: Modernize and customize the customer-facing experience by updating the homepage, car listing (product) page, blog pages, and overall shop theme.

**Stories:**
- Story 1.1: Redesign and implement the homepage with new layout, banners, and featured sections
- Story 1.2: Update the product (car list) page to improve car browsing, filtering, and visual presentation
- Story 1.3: Create or update blog pages for content marketing and SEO
- Story 1.4: Customize the shop theme (colors, typography, layout) to match brand identity and improve UX
- Story 1.5: Apply color, font, and branding
- Story 1.6: Test responsiveness and accessibility
- Story 1.7: Finalize and activate theme

### Story 1.1: Redesign and implement the homepage with new layout, banners, and featured sections

**As a** visitor or returning customer,
**I want** to see a modern, visually appealing homepage with clear navigation, banners, and featured car sections,
**So that** I can quickly understand the value proposition, browse cars, and access key site areas.

**Requirements:**
- Responsive layout for desktop, tablet, and mobile
- Hero/banner section with promotional image and call-to-action
- Featured cars section (e.g., “Popular Rentals” or “New Arrivals”)
- Quick links to car list, registration, and blog
- Section for customer testimonials or trust signals
- Blog/news preview section (latest 2-3 posts)
- Footer with contact info, social links, and legal
- Theme colors, fonts, and branding consistent with company identity

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Given I visit the homepage on any device
  When the page loads
  Then I see a hero/banner section with a prominent call-to-action
  And I see a featured cars section with at least 3 cars displayed
  And I see navigation links to car list, registration, and blog
  And I see a preview of the latest blog posts
  And I see a footer with contact info and social links
- Given I resize the browser or use a mobile device
  When the homepage loads
  Then all sections are readable and visually appealing (responsive)
- Given the homepage is loaded
  When I click a featured car
  Then I am taken to the car’s detail page
- Given the homepage is loaded
  When I click the registration or blog link
  Then I am taken to the correct page
- Given the homepage is loaded
  When I view the theme
  Then colors, fonts, and layout match the brand guidelines

---

### Story 1.2: Scaffold custom Bagisto theme package

**Requirements:**
- Create `packages/Webkul/AutoLeadingTheme/` with standard Bagisto theme structure
- Set up Blade views, assets, config, and Vite bundling
- Register theme in Bagisto config

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Theme package exists and is recognized by Bagisto
- Theme can be set as default in admin

---

### Story 1.3: Build homepage layout and shared components

**Requirements:**
- Implement homepage structure (hero, search, featured cars, brands, services, process, blog/FAQ/contact, footer)
- Create reusable Blade components for cards, banners, navigation, etc.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Homepage matches reference design visually and functionally
- Components are reusable across pages

---

### Story 1.4: Implement all referenced pages and sections

**Requirements:**
- Car list, car detail, brand filter, blog/news, FAQ, contact, registration/login, rental process, service commitment
- Ensure navigation and routing work as expected

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- All pages are accessible and match design
- Navigation is consistent and functional

---

### Story 1.5: Apply color, font, and branding

**Requirements:**
- Use correct color palette, typography, and logo
- Style buttons, headings, and cards per design

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Visuals match reference site and brand guidelines

---

### Story 1.6: Test responsiveness and accessibility

**Requirements:**
- Ensure layouts work on all device sizes
- Check color contrast and keyboard navigation

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Theme is fully responsive and accessible

---

### Story 1.7: Finalize and activate theme

**Requirements:**
- Bundle assets with Vite
- Set theme as default in Bagisto
- Document customization points (color/logo swap, Blade sections)

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Theme is live and ready for production use
- Documentation is available for future updates

